entries.title: Lebanon to restore UN payments 'immediately' after losing voting rights in General Assembly
entries.description: Lebanon vowed to restore its payments to the UN's operating budget on Friday after losing its right to vote in the 193-member UN General Assembly, according to the country's state-owned National News Agency (NNA).

entries.title: From the Emirates to Davos: South Korea's big week in global business
entries.description: South Korea's leader is capping off a whirlwind week, after securing tens of billions of dollars in investment from the Middle East and vowing to have his country play a more important role in revitalizing international supply chains.

entries.title: Japan considers downgrading Covid-19 to same level as seasonal flu
entries.description: Japan will consider downgrading Covid-19 to the same category as seasonal influenza this spring, Prime Minister Fumio Kishida announced Friday.

entries.title: The death of an American attorney at a Mexico hotel did not show signs of violence, official says
entries.description: Mexican authorities investigating the case of an American attorney who was found dead at a resort hotel earlier this month determined there was no foul play in his death, according to an official statement released Thursday.

entries.title: FTX founder says there was a security incident at parents' home
entries.description: Attorneys for disgraced FTX founder Sam Bankman-Fried urged the judge in his fraud case to keep the names of two people who co-signed his $250 million bond secret because of actual threats he says his family has received.
